      "writtenOn": "2026-03-20T06:57:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Gary, thanks for the fix. I have some thoughts inline.\n\nRegarding:\n\n\u003e Raising PLDM_FIRMWARE_MAX_STRING to 255 is a separate change that affects struct sizes across the firmware update ABI — I think that warrants its own patch with maintainer input.\n\nIt warrants its own patch, however the ABI concern is not yet great because the only functions using the struct are marked `LIBPLDM_ABI_TESTING`. While that\u0027s the case we can make changes as we see fit.\n\nHowever, 64 was chosen as a \"reasonable\" value for static storage in the context of the library\u0027s use in freestanding embedded environments, and so changes do warrant some discussion.",
      "revId": "d7ef54e6fb3d7636037cb23f8ff4dc703f96f8b7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
